      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental data from Hariharan et al. (2011) documents flow rates, rotational speeds, and fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture, viscosity 0.00356 Pa·s at 25°C). Simulation boundary conditions match experimental values within 1.5% for all five operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., mean relative error, validation metric u_val) computed and reported for NIH predictions versus experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error in NIH across all five operating points is 8.3%. The validation metric u_val computed per ASME V&V 20 is 0.094, indicating acceptable agreement for MRL 2. Worst-case point (2 L/min, 2000 RPM) shows 12.1% relative error, attributed to transitional flow regime effects."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoI (NIH) is directly used to compute the decision QoI (RH). Mapping from NIH to RH is documented with no intermediate untested transformations.",
      "rationale": "NIH is computed directly from CFD shear stress history integrated along pathlines using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. RH is the direct ratio of candidate NIH to predicate NIH under identical operating conditions, requiring no additional model transformations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions span the COU operating envelope. At least 4 of 5 COU operating points have a corresponding experimental validation point within 15% of flow rate and rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares the same impeller topology as the candidate device. All 5 COU operating points (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) are within the validated operating envelope. Geometric similarity confirmed by impeller-to-volute clearance ratio within 8%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
